President Obama has appointed Rashad Hussain as his Special Envoy to the Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC), the second largest inter-governmental organization in the world. This appointment aims to deepen and expand partnerships with Muslims around the world. Hussain, who is currently Deputy Associate Counsel to President Obama, has been involved in national security, new media, and science and technology issues. He has also worked on the New Beginning initiative outlined by President Obama in his 2009 address in Cairo. Hussain is a respected member of the American Muslim community and has a background in law, with degrees from Yale Law School and Harvard University.